race.comment: RASPUTINA (7) finished third two runs back at Wycheproof then improved last time out to score by 4 lengths over 2000m at Mildura. Christine Puls scored on her last time and retains the mount. Stepping up a level this time but on current form she is capable of another big performance. AMERICAN GAS (2) made progress last time out, finishing 2 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 2000m at Mortlake. Likely improver with strong prospects. MUMMSIE (11) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1800m at Wycheproof, beaten 3 lengths into sixth. Suitably placed so can turn things around. PROPRIETARY (3) drifted well back and failed to finish it off last start when tenth, beaten 6 lengths, over 1300m at Swan Hill. Won't find this as tough so he is perfectly placed to score.
